<p><b>David Carson</b> is an American <a href="/wiki/Graphic_designer" title="Graphic designer">graphic designer</a>. He is best known for his innovative magazine design, and use of experimental <a href="/wiki/Typography" title="Typography">typography</a>. He was the art director for the magazine <i><a href="/wiki/Ray_Gun_(magazine)" title="Ray Gun (magazine)">Ray Gun</a></i>. Carson was perhaps the most influential graphic designer of the nineties. In particular, his widely-imitated aesthetic defined the so-called "grunge" era.<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since May 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></p>
